T*
(How A Fellow Should Work Each Week) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Start from master.) Tj
T*
(2. Create a focused branch.) Tj
T*
(3. Read the weekly paper or technical source.) Tj
T*
(4. Write a paper note or learning log.) Tj
T*
(5. Create a design outcome if a decision is needed.) Tj
T*
(6. Build the smallest useful output.) Tj
T*
(7. Verify it with a test, benchmark, screenshot, command output, or manual review.) Tj
T*
(8. Update the weekly report.) Tj
T*
(9. Run the verification script.) Tj
T*
(10. Open a pull request.) Tj
T*
(11. Review with another person.) Tj
T*
(12. Merge only when the work is understandable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
